<h2>Common Causes of Dull and Uneven Skin</h2>

<h3>Sun Exposure</h3>

<p>
UV radiation is one of the leading causes of pigmentation and premature skin aging. Even brief daily exposure can contribute to dark spots, uneven skin tone, and loss of radiance.
</p>

<h3>Environmental Pollution</h3>

<p>
Airborne pollutants can accumulate on the skin's surface, contributing to congestion and dullness.
</p>

<h3>Dehydration</h3>

<p>
Dehydrated skin often appears tired, rough, and less luminous. Hydration is essential for maintaining a healthy glow.
</p>

<h3>Dead Skin Cell Build-Up</h3>

<p>
Over time, dead skin cells accumulate on the skin's surface, preventing light from reflecting evenly. Professional treatments help remove this buildup and reveal fresher skin underneath.
</p>

<h3>Lifestyle Factors</h3>

<p>
Poor sleep, stress, diet, and inadequate skincare can all affect skin health and contribute to dullness.
</p>

